This piece is about standing back up after every time you get the wind knocked tf out of you by life. We’ve all been through something we thought we wouldn’t survive, whether it be heartbreak, grief, trauma, betrayal…and we are all still here. You’ve survived 100% of your worst days, and maybe the best thing that heartbreak can teach us, is that nothing can actually break us. Fucked up shit might change us, rearrange our insides for a bit, and catapult us into growth, but as long as you’re still breathing you’re still invincible. As long as you don’t leave yourself - you’re unbreakable ❤️‍🔥

*moves to Greece 🇬🇷 

This mini break in Santorini was so needed for my body and mind. Tour has been so incredible and has moved so fast, but here I was able to slow down my pace and just feel grateful for it all. Grateful for dance and movement - my greatest healers, for my body - my greatest instrument, all the students who have come and shared their energy and love with me so far, and my family and loves who support and cheer me on as I travel Europe solo dolo 🙏🏼✨

Three more countries left!! We begin again tomorrow… 

#takingmyselfontour

My second class in Paris with @35_events ❤️‍🔥

I loved teaching this combo on tour because it gives the opportunity to bring a darker side of femininity to movement. Sometimes you gotta bring your demons to the dance floor in order to set them free. While dancing sexy is obviously very fun, it is also an opportunity to dive deep and heal some very real shit, but in order to heal it you have to feel it, no matter how heavy/chaotic/toxic it may be. 

Thank you to @35_events for having me and for initiating my entire EU tour! It was @gizem.hnl who encouraged me to teach all over Europe, and I am so grateful to her for helping me set it all into motion. A true queen 🙏🏼❤️‍🔥

#takingmyselfontour #kaylabrendachoreography #vigilanteshit #taylorswift

Im home from my first ever EU teaching tour, and I am so grateful, heart so full, so amazed at the humans I met, and also so proud of myself. 

Before I left I was telling my close friends that this was my “Dance, eat, pray, love” tour, bc I just had a feeling that going all over Europe solo dolo was going to be an important journey in all the ways. I needed a journey within myself. I could feel it. I needed to meet myself again, and dance is my greatest teacher and healer, so hey 11 classes in 9 countries let’s mf go😅

It was unexpected to me, and so moving, to find that most of “meeting myself” on this journey didn’t even really come from dancing, but from all the dancers and organizers that shared with me with so much emotion how my class, words, BodyLove, art, has impacted them. Girls had screenshots of my IG captions as the background on their phones, or had been in my first BODYLOVE Series and said it saved their life. Some danced with me thru COVID online and said it got them through, and some i just met and had reignited their passion and love for themselves in my class. Each and every love note they came to me with was like a shining reminder saying THIS IS WHO YOU ARE. 

I am overwhelmed with this amount of love, and I will remember it forever. It has chased the clouds away and reminded me that my
purpose is to SHINE ☀️✨ I feel so full, so humbled, so grateful, so absolutely moved. 

I thought I needed to meet myself again, but in reality I just needed to be reminded of who I already am. 

Thank you to all my Europe girlies for the love notes. Truly. I hope I was able to give to you as much as you gave to me 🙏🏼💕

#takingmyselfontour

Slow and se✖️y 🥵

I was writing in my journal today about how I have discovered a new boundary within myself, and the boundary applies to “rushing”. That shit exhausts me.  I feel the pressure to rush in so many aspects of life. Rushed to wake up, rushed to get to work, rushed to make money, rushed to finish what I’m saying, rushed to get turned on. The world around us wants us to go faster faster faster, and so clearly my body is saying “No. Slower.” 
Just a breath slower, really. Slower so I can feel, slower for more intentionality, slower for more SENSUALITY. Slower to create more spaciousness. Slower for more of my senses to be activated by every magical and confusing wisp of this life. 
Slow and se✖️y wins the race 😉❤️‍🔥 Give me all of the juicy in-betweens 🌊 🌊

“Inside every woman there is a lioness, a wild woman, a priestess, a witch, a seductress, a siren, a sorceress. The world’s messaging tells us that such things are “evil”, “unladylike”, and deserving of literal death. The severity of this programming has manipulated, threatened, and convinced us in countless ways to disconnect from our innate inner wisdom, power, sensuality, and miraculous bodies in general. I hope this movement, song, and moment can help you connect once again to your magic. And I don’t mean magic like fairy dust and glitter… I mean magic like fire and desire and deep relationship with self. I mean magic like witchy full moon ritual vibes that lay the groundwork for deep transformation and liberation of any part of you that seeks to renew and re-wild. There are no rules with this one. Feel into the vibe and the song, and then follow whatever expression wants to come out. Dress up, dress down... WHATEVER YOU WANT BESTIE. Have a moment. Go wild for awhile. Get moody.”

I’m so excited to bring you ESSENTIALS: INTRO TO TWERK with @yelusballestass 💕

Hearing Yelus explain Twerk gave me so much insight to this style and how the mindset behind Twerk is so on brand for bodylove ie: it’s necessary for successful twerking to relax your body and your muscles SO THEY CAN MOVE AND SHAKE. Twerk = skin moving. As women I’m sure we all have experienced tensing up, holding everything “in”, and contorting our bodies as to not make our skin fold, shake, or move. BUT with Twerk, you learn to embrace those things, and they actually become your power! How beautiful. 

So I just have one question… ARE YALL READY TO SHAKE SOME ASS!?!? 🍑🍑🍑

MUDDY FEET ✨
The work in this piece is all about giving yourself permission to access your anger. 
It’s about getting comfortable with the most firey, uncomfortable, ravenous fury within you, and allowing it to have a voice for awhile.
We’ve gotten almost too good at suppressing our anger. We might feel it momentarily, but then we hide it away deep within our bellies. Somewhere along the way we’ve been taught that this is what a good woman does. 
Anger cannot live here. Anger cannot rule.
But I think anger and rage are some of the greatest messengers in this life. We mistake anger as being FOR someone else, but it never is. Our anger is for us. Our rage is for us. 
Anger, rage, and fury are messengers showing us where we have loved, where we have cared, where we were innocent and mistreated, where our boundaries have been disgustingly violated, and where something is just fucking WRONG. 
Anger, rage, and fury are the guardians of our vulnerability. 
And sometimes they need to be FULLY felt, in every cell of our body, so we can learn what we were meant to learn, and heal what we are meant to heal. 🖤

As far as the unfolding of my life, I have always felt my internal compass first, before my direction adjusts on the outside. I’ll feel something shift -a nudge, a knowing- within me, and then I use movement as a way to experience whatever that is within the safety of my body. Once I know what it feels like, I can make the decisions in work, relationships, schedules, etc. to reflect the honesty of my inner compass. This is how it has always been, and I’m so grateful for the gift of movement. To be a mover. To have this body that holds so much knowing-ness and wisdom. 🖤 
I love dance. And that’s all.

I was sitting at the front of the room watching, and was literally feeling blasted by honesty and raw feminine power. I wanna thank @tayteii_ for not only bringing me to AUS but also for cultivating a community and an environment that felt so free and so “home” for me. The work in this Advanced Heels piece isn’t about nailing every step and detail perfectly, the work in this piece is about letting your sensual energy flow and move through you, and drench every inch of your body and soul 🌊.⁠
⁠
We spend so much time as women monitoring the flow of our sensual energy. Trying to make sure it’s perceived correctly. ⁠
⁠
Trying to make sure it doesn’t put us in danger. Trying to make sure we’re viewed as humans of “value” before being viewed as sensual, sexual, enchanted portals to the divine… as if being “of value” and sensual are mutually exclusive. They are not.⁠
⁠
The work in this piece is to release the monitoring momentarily. Let the fountain flow.⁠
⁠
Put yourself in a safe space, a vibey space, and tune out the world as you tune IN to the goddess energy that roars like a waterfall within you. ⁠
⁠
Trust what comes up and comes through.⁠
⁠
Let yourself feel.⁠
⁠
And flow.⁠
⁠
And drench. ⁠
⁠
